# After `npx eas-cli init`, copy the project UUID from the Expo dashboard (or from
# `eas project:info`) into one of:
#
#   • A repo-root file named `.eas-project-id` (one line, no quotes), for local builds, or
#   • The `EAS_PROJECT_ID` environment variable, or
#   • The GitHub Actions secret `EAS_PROJECT_ID` (used by `.github/workflows/eas-android-preview.yml`).
#
# Cursor Cloud Agent shells do not inject Cursor "secrets" as env vars; use GitHub Actions
# with repository secrets `EXPO_TOKEN` + `EAS_PROJECT_ID`, or run `eas build` on your machine.
